    <main id="main-doc">
        <section id="Introduction" class="main-section">
            <header>Introduction</header>
            <p>Welcome to the technical documentation page. Here you'll learn the basics of web development.</p>
            <p>Web development involves HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
            <code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code>
            <p>HTML provides structure, CSS adds style, and JavaScript enables interactivity.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="HTML_Basics" class="main-section">
            <header>HTML Basics</header>
            <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the foundation of web pages.</p>
            <p>It uses elements like headings, paragraphs, and lists to structure content.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>&lt;h1&gt; for main headings</li>
                <li>&lt;p&gt; for paragraphs</li>
                <li>&lt;ul&gt; and &lt;li&gt; for lists</li>
            </ul>
            <code>&lt;h1&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;</code>
            <p>HTML attributes provide additional information about elements.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="CSS_Basics" class="main-section">
            <header>CSS Basics</header>
            <p>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style web pages.</p>
            <p>You can define colors, fonts, layouts, and more using CSS.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Selectors target elements</li>
                <li>Properties define styles</li>
                <li>Values specify the style</li>
            </ul>
            <code>body { background-color: #f4f4f9; }</code>
            <p>CSS can be inline, internal, or external.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="JavaScript_Basics" class="main-section">
            <header>JavaScript Basics</header>
            <p>JavaScript makes web pages interactive.</p>
            <p>You can manipulate HTML elements, handle events, and perform calculations.</p>
            <code>document.getElementById('example').innerHTML = 'Hello!';</code>
            <p>JavaScript is a versatile language that runs in the browser.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="Advanced_Topics" class="main-section">
            <header>Advanced Topics</header>
            <p>Advanced topics include frameworks, APIs, and responsive design.</p>
            <p>Frameworks like React and Angular make development faster.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>APIs allow communication between systems</li>
                <li>Responsive design adapts to screen sizes</li>
            </ul>
            <code>@media (max-width: 600px) { body { font-size: 14px; } }</code>
            <p>Continue exploring to master web development.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
